{"lastModified":1774346841380,"uri":"c::9938368400::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d","yachtType":["Power Catamaran","Motor"],"description":"Winter Base Port: St Marteen\nSummer Base Port: Bonifacio\n\nOperating Area: \nWinter 2025/2026 - Leeward Islands\nSummer 2026 - Corsica, French Riviera & Monaco, Italy - Sardinia\n\nDouble Happiness, a magnificent 60 Sunreef Power Eco, strikes the perfect balance between luxury, performance, and eco-friendly cruising. Designed with both comfort and sustainability in mind, she boasts a spacious layout that provide a haven of tranquility, while the expansive living areas offer ample space for relaxation and entertainment.\n\nThe yacht’s interiors exude contemporary elegance, featuring refined decor, designer furniture, and light natural fabrics. Panoramic glazing in the main salon floods the space with natural light, enhancing the feeling of openness and connection with the surrounding seascape.\n\nOutdoor living is a true highlight aboard Double Happiness. The full-beam aft cockpit presents a fantastic alfresco dining area with breathtaking ocean views, complemented by a daybed, bar, and a hydraulic platform perfect for sunbathing and easy access to water activities. serene bow terrace and a well-equipped flybridge with modular seating and barbecue complete the outdoor spaces, perfect for entertaining and relaxation.\n\nDouble Happiness promises an exhilarating yet relaxing charter experience. The professional crew of three ensures impeccable service throughout your journey.","blueprint":{"name":"DOUBLE HAPPINESS","images":["/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::07e7ebd0-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::081a6d80-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::07c129f0-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::07b03a00-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::07c2d7a0-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::07e57ad0-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::07e63e20-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::082f7c20-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::07e6b350-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::07ae1720-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::07d3c790-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}","/media/media::image::a::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::07e70170-b0df-11ef-a508-e18c3b7c20e8/{imageVariant}"],"make":"Sunreef Yachts","model":"60 Sunreef Power Eco","maxCrew":3,"sleeps":8,"basePort":{"uri":"a::place::d51ce65a-b3ed-11ed-b35b-325096b39f47","name":"Bonifacio","coordinates":{"latitude":41.38905215189958,"longitude":9.15999176158211},"country":"France"},"cruisingCapacity":12,"staticCapacity":0,"builtYear":2024,"architect":"Sunreef Yachts","topSpeed":0,"cruiseSpeed":8,"cabinLayout":[{"label":"Double Cabins","value":"4"}],"cabins":4,"bathrooms":4,"length":18.03,"beam":10.7,"draft":1.5,"hullType":"Multi hull","hullConstruction":"Composite","tonnage":60,"superStructure":["Flybridge"],"engines":"2 x Engiro 370W at 622 V DC","amenities":[{"label":"Daybed"},{"label":"Bar"},{"label":"Hydraulic platform"},{"label":"Flybridge"},{"label":"Barbecue"}],"toys":[{"label":"SUP"},{"label":"Water Skis"},{"label":"Wakeboard"},{"label":"Inflatable Jobe"},{"label":"Paddle Board","quantity":"2"},{"label":"Seabob"},{"label":"Foil board"},{"label":"Electric Bicycles","quantity":"2"},{"label":"Electric Scooters","quantity":"2"}],"entertainment":[],"tenders":[]},"crew":[{"name":"Julien Roudaut","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::9938368400::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::35cef680-45f7-11f0-9ae1-fb1fa2e410f1/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Nationality: French\nLanguages: English, French, Italian, Portuguese, Spanish\n\nDescription:\nCaptain Julien brings over 30 years of experience in coastal and ocean navigation, with an extensive background commanding both private and charter yachts across the Mediterranean, Caribbean, and beyond. Holding an MCA Master 500 GT license, Julien is a seasoned and multi-talented captain with deep expertise in yacht refits, deliveries, and technical management.\n\nFluent in five languages and passionate about watersports—including kitesurfing, wingfoiling, and diving —Julien brings both technical proficiency and a vibrant energy to every charter. His prior roles span an impressive range of vessels including Perini Navi, Swan, Lagoon, and Sunseeker yachts, and he has successfully completed multiple Atlantic crossings.\n\nBeyond his maritime credentials, Julien has a formal education in marketing and digital communication, and brings a refined sense of service and guest satisfaction to his leadership on board. Known for his calm demeanor, problem-solving skills, and attention to detail, Julien ensures a smooth, luxurious, and memorable experience for all guests."},{"name":"Nuria Munoz","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::9938368400::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::7bfa1130-45f7-11f0-9ae1-fb1fa2e410f1/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Nationality: Spanish\nLanguages: English, French, Spanish\n\nDescription:\nNuria is a passionate and versatile stewardess and cook who brings a warm, guest-focused energy to life on board. With a rich background in Mediterranean and Andalusian cuisine, she designs flavorful, health-conscious menus tailored to guests’ preferences and dietary needs. Her dedication to culinary excellence ensures each meal becomes a memorable part of the charter experience.\n\nIn addition to her galley skills, Nuria has over 23 years of experience as a personal trainer and wellness coach, which enhances her ability to provide holistic, attentive care to guests. She holds certifications in STCW Basic Safety Training, Food Handling, and Health Consulting, and is always committed to maintaining the highest standards of cleanliness, organization, and service.\n\nFluent in Spanish and proficient in both English and French, Nuria is known for her adaptability, reliability, and positive attitude. Her goal is to create an atmosphere on board where guests feel truly cared for— through thoughtful service, delicious food, and attention to every detail."},{"name":"Kaylan Bekker","avatar":"/media/media::image::c::9938368400::vessel::7e274ae0-b0dd-11ef-8d44-b1bb7846f71d::assets::cfbf8a70-e4b7-11f0-9ac9-d19067053cdf/{imageVariant}","role":"Captain","bio":"Kaylan is a professional Stewardess with hands-on experience working on board a catamaran. She is confident managing all aspects of guest care and interior service, while also supporting deck operations to ensure a smooth and enjoyable charter experience.\n\nWith a background that includes teaching and childcare experience, Kaylan is particularly comfortable working with families while maintaining a polished and professional approach suited to all charter guests. She brings a calm, adaptable, and energetic presence onboard, creating a welcoming and well-organised environment.\n\nHer experience includes high-standard housekeeping, table service, cocktail and wine preparation, speciality coffee service, tender operations, and guest excursions. Known for her attention to detail and proactive mindset, Kaylan takes pride in anticipating guest needs and delivering thoughtful service throughout each charter.\n\nKaylan also enjoys capturing guests’ experiences through photography and drone videography, creating lasting memories of their time onboard. Professional, reliable, and personable, she is committed to contributing to memorable and seamless charter experiences."}],"pricing":{"weekPricingFrom":{"currency":"EUR","price":4800000,"displayCurrency":"EUR","displayPrice":4800000,"unit":"WEEK"},"weekPricingTo":{"currency":"USD","price":5900000,"displayCurrency":"USD","displayPrice":5900000,"unit":"WEEK"},"pricingInfo":[{"name":"Summer: Mediterranean - High Season","effectiveDates":[{"from":"2026-06-14T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2026-09-15T23:59:59.999Z"},{"from":"2027-06-14T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2027-09-15T23:59:59.999Z"},{"from":"2028-06-14T00:00:00.000Z","to":"2028-09-15T23:59:59.999Z"}],"pricing":{"currency":"EUR","charterFee":5200000,"inputAmountTaxed":"EXCLUSIVE","note":"","unit":"WEEK","lineItems":[{"item":"Charter Fee","quantity":1,"unitPrice":5200000,"amount":5200000,"conditions":"VAT & APA Excluded"},{"item":"APA","conditions":"","quantity":0.25,"unitPrice":5200000,"amount":1300000}],"total":6500000,"subTotal":6500000,"totalTax":0},"inclusionZones":[{"label":"Corsica","type":"Geo subunit","category":["Europe","Southern Europe","Corsica"],"coordinates":[9.104917129771797,42.161865413836736],"bbox":[8.565625000000011,41.384912109374994,9.556445312500017,43.021484375]},{"label":"France","type":"Country","category":["Europe","Western Europe","France"],"coordinates":[-3.676762491181631,13.257370810531999],"bbox":[-61.79784094999991,-21.37078215899993,55.854502800000034,51.08754088371883]},{"label":"Sardinia","type":"Geo subunit","category":["Europe","Southern Europe","Sardinia"],"coordinates":[8.96574354539669,40.12242872762209],"bbox":[8.180859375000011,38.90966796875,9.805273437500006,41.257080078125]},{"label":"Monaco","type":"Sovereign country","category":["Europe","Western Europe","Monac